location: Palm Beach Gardens, Palm Beach, South Florida
postcontent:
Up for grabs is my never fired (only @ PSA for function testing) PSA Dissaptor. I've been holding onto it in the safe but really have no use for it. Not desperate to sell. $850. No trades please. FTF in Palm Beach Gardens. CWP Preffered and must sign Bill of Sale. Can ship to your FFL for $50. 

Magpul MOE K Grip
MOE Stock
PSA Detachable Carry Handle
2x Magpul Gen M3 PMAGs


DETAILS
Once upon a time, a "dissipator" AR was created by taking a 20" rifle-length gas system upper and cutting the barrel down to 16".  This allowed the shooter to keep the long sight radius of a rifle for accuracy, but keep the carbine length barrel for maneuverability.  The proximity of the gas port to the muzzle, however, played havoc with timing and made reliability a hit or miss proposition.   Advances in AR technology  have produced reliable carbine and mid-length gas systems, that can be hidden using low-profile gas blocks.  This allows for a front sight base to be pinned in the rifle position for the longer sight radius without the worry of the unorthodox gas port location affecting operation.   We use the term "mock" to differentiate our dissipator from a cut-down rifle length version.  Our Premium Mid-length mock dissipator uses a  Chrome Moly Vanadium steel barrel that is chrome-lined for durability.

Barrel:  16" mil-spec steel barrel, chrome lined and chambered in 5.56 NATO, with a 1/7 twist, M4 barrel extension, and a Mid-length gas system with a low-profile gas block.   Medium profile barrel is proof tested, magnetic particle inspected, phosphate coated, and  finished off with a pinned F-marked front sight post in the Rifle position with sling swivel, rifle length handguards, and A2 flash hider.  Barrel is made for us by FN Manufacturing here in Columbia SC.

Upper: Forged 7075-T6 A3 AR upper is made to MIL-SPECS and hard coat anodized black for durability. Featuring machined T marks, and a mil-spec finish. These uppers are made for us right here in the USA by a mil-spec manufacturer.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Czechpoint VZ-58 Folder 7.62x39 w/ ammo
postcontent:
Still has 4 years left on its 5 year transferable warranty. Czechpoint is still backordered for months. Round count is very low (~300). Runs perfectly with all the ammo I tried (Tula, Wolf, GT). 

Vz58 aren't aks. They are much smaller, lighter, softer shooting than a stamped AK but built on a stronger milled receiver and can be fed with stripper clips due to open top design. The czechs know their firearms and told the ussr pre cold war that they would not be converting to the ak47. The vz design was originally designed for a larger battle rifle round but shrunk to accomodate the ussr's desire for 7.62x39.

Gun has a nice smooth trigger. Stock can be worked one handed unlike ACE folders which need you to jam your pistol grip into your gut to get more leverage. Has the lacquered finish Waffen Works is known for. Added a lot of extras to the gun. 

VZ-58. Chambered in 7.62. Distributed by Czechpoint USA, originally converted by Waffen Works.

Camdenton/Linn Creek

FS: made in September of 1967 Revelations model 120 18 shot semi auto .22 LR. made for Western Auto by Marlin. This is essentially the same as a first generation model 60 with a very minor change or 2. Like the front bronze bead/blade sight rather than the hooded ramp found on the Marlin 60. From the research i have done, this model is less commonly encountered than the first model Marlin 60. I picked it up with the intent of keeping it, but the household finances say otherwise. So someone is going to get a damned fine rifle. 

21" barrel, 40 1/2" total length. Weight is only about 4lbs or so.This is in original non refinished condition. I have personally taken it completely down, cleaned, serviced and function checked for reliability. It is in my opinion 90% condition with only some very minor rust freckles here & there on the barrel, nothing drastic at all. The stock is more on the blond side of things and is also in very good plus condition. 

It is wearing a Weaver B4 scope with see through scope mounts, meaning you can use the scope or original iron sights as desired. I tried to get a shot of the 'peep through' feature, but it was tough to pull off one handed and work the camera at the same time...lol, but I think you will get the idea.

I took it out this morning and ran another 2 tubes for fun. The target pic below is the result. 50 yards, the left was the initial sight in with a stray round or 2 from my arm wiggle. The right is shooting as fast as my finger could pull the trigger. This is one hell of a nice shooter, smooth clean & crisp action. I hate to sell it but bills have to be paid.

I am not able to drive any more, so you will have to come out to Linn Creek to pick it up, where you will also have the opportunity to shoot it for yourself before you take it home.

Yours $200 with the scope. $175 without.

I have 10 detailed pics, message me to see them.

title: For Sale:  Early 19th century Japanese matchlock with inlay barrel and beautiful wood
location: Cary, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Up for sale is a beautiful Japanese matchlock musket. It measures 51 1/2" in length and has brass, copper and silver inlay in the barrel. There is kanji on it that says "Tsuruga prefecture" and has a westerner shaped figure holding some intertwining scrollwork along with a crane in silver. There are three other spots where there is decorative scrollwork.

The stock is beautiful burlwood with some great grain showing and it was registered in 1872 due to the kanji written on the stock. It has 壬申 二五六四号　免 (Meiji 5th year registration number 2564). 

The lock works and functions fine with no issues. The ramrod is present and the original piece. Overall, it is a great piece!

I am asking $1300. I prefer to meet in the Cary area but will consider just about anywhere in the triangle. I will ship, but payment must be by paypal and all fees and shipping costs covered by the buyer.

postcontent:
Racal Acoustics RAPTOR H-387/VRC Headset MBITR PTT SINCGARS RA5000/1/6400 ANR

You're looking at a used working condition Racal Acoustics RAPTOR H-387/VRC Headset (model RA5000/1/6400) with a PTT (Push-to-Talk).  It can be used with AN/PRC-148 MBITR with the included coiled adapter cable.  The RA5000 Raptor headset has been designed specifically for use in tactical wheeled vehicles where highly intelligible communications are essential over extended periods of time.

The Active Noise Reduction (ANR) technology employed by the RA5000 Raptor is very effective at reducing the unwanted noise generated in these vehicles, especially when travelling at medium to high speeds.
Key Features
Passive and Active Noise Reduction. NRR greater than 22dB(A) 
Racal Acoustics Electronic Talk-Through (Single, internal 'AA' battery) 
Napeband 'around-the-neck' or Headband 'over-the-head' attachments 
Environmentally qualified to military standards 
Certified to operate in electromagnetic field strengths up to 50v/m 
Reversible noise cancelling microphone & switchbox 
Separate input for respirator microphone 
Compatible with a wide range of Vehicle Intercom Systems 

Benefits

The RA5000 Raptor Series of headsets are not simply an evolution in military headset design but are more of a paradigm shift in concept and approach.

The aspects of quality, highly intelligible speech for both received and transmitted communications, reliability and ruggedness were prerequisites for a new product design by Racal Acoustics. But for this product, military personnel (the end user) had specifically cited comfort and compatibility with existing equipment such as small arms and ballistic protective equipment as top priorities.

Each component within the headset is a new design, incorporating the vast experience that Racal has developed exclusively within the military communications arena.

The acoustic ear shells have been designed not only to be compatible with the Advance Combat Helmet (ACH) but to provide the highest achievable level of acoustic performance integrity. The benefit of this is that it has been possible to reduce the force which the headset clamps to the users head resulting in a much more comfortable experience.

title: For Sale:  1943 Ishvesk ex-sniper 91/30 Mosin Nagant FS
postcontent: Earlier import 1943 Ishvesk 91/30 ex-sniper rifle. Brief history: When the USSR adopted the SVD, many of the PU sniper rifles were returned to Infantry rifle configuration by grinding off the scope mounting screws flush with the reciever (pic 2 shows the screws), filling the gaps with weld and bluing over the top. Returning to Sniper configuration is relatively straightforward, with high-quality reproduction scopes and mounts available from a firm called Accumounts. Postwar stock, and small Century Arms import mark near muzzle. Finish is very good, stock is excellent and bore is sharp and presents little if any wear. Not your run of the mill Mosin, easy restoration or should prove VERY accurate as-is. To be selected as a Sniper, it had to be able to put 10 shots in just over 1" at 100m. Respond to ad or call/text ate six 5  405 67 oh 4.
